        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Claims-based identity is a common way for applications to acquire the identity information they need about users inside their organization, in other organizations, and on the Internet. It also provides a consistent approach for applications running on-premises or in the cloud. Claims-based identity abstracts the individual elements of identity and access control into two parts: a notion of claims, and the concept of an issuer or an authority - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Claims-based_identity wikipedia]"
